                <header class="comment-header">
                    <cite class="author_name heading" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" ><cite class="comment_author_name" itemprop="name" >Kevin Diffily</cite></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>                    
                    <!-- display the comment metadata like time and date-->
                        <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
                            <a href="http://www.openhomeautomation.net/arduino-vs-raspberry-pi-which-platform-is-the-best-for-home-automation/#comment-78508">
                                <time  itemprop="commentTime" itemscope="itemscope" datetime="2013-04-29T01:52:15+00:00" >
                                    July 10, 2014 at 12:23 am                                </time>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                </header>

                <!-- display the comment text -->
                <div class='comment_text entry-content-wrapper clearfix'  itemprop="commentText" >
                <p>I think the real weakness with the arduino price wise is once you figure in the cost of any wireless board it is pretty expensive.  Almost better off using a Pi RevA with a $10 bluetooth or wifi adaptor.</p>
                                <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/arduino-vs-raspberry-pi-which-platform-is-the-best-for-home-automation/?replytocom=78508#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-78508", "78508", "respond", "282")'>Reply</a>                </div>
