<p>Thanks a lot for this interesting comment. I totally agree that for a home automation project that will cover a large home and will last for years, the setup time doesn&#8217;t matter, and for this reason the Pi + Arduinos connected to it is an obvious choice. However, many of my readers are also using home automation on a much smaller scale to learn about Arduino &#038; basic electronics, so I wanted to consider all sorts of home automation projects in this article.</p>
